Notebook[{
Cell["The Stabilizer Formalism, by Computation", "Title",ExpressionUUID->"7bd625c5-f1e5-4ef5-9d60-4690776828a5"],

Cell["\<\
This document teaches the stabilizer formalism the way one would teach it at \
a chalkboard with a kernel open: every claim is immediately computed. We \
start from the observation that a single qubit can be specified not by its \
two amplitudes but by the one operator that fixes it, build that idea into \
the Aaronson-Gottesman tableau, and ride it all the way to thousand-qubit \
Clifford circuits, error-correcting codes, graph states, magic states, and \
Clifford channels. We close with a measured, honest comparison against the \
specialized C++ and Julia stabilizer simulators.\
\>", "Text",ExpressionUUID->"80bf328b-87f7-4d04-8474-5380b40ef227"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "The arc is: a state is what stabilizes it (single qubit), ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  StyleBox["n", "TI"]], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "6ed7118e-e47d-4e4b-8e92-b4705d791a17"],
 " generators replace ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  SuperscriptBox["2", 
   StyleBox["n", "TI"]]], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "794982a1-0f6f-4864-8464-4f5e63c37567"],
 " amplitudes (the tableau), entanglement and measurement become linear \
algebra over ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  SubscriptBox["\|01d53d", "2"]], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "7a07269b-c76c-4d7c-86f0-c6b6fc96fc4e"],
 " (the field of two elements ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  RowBox[{
   RowBox[{"{", "0"}], ",", 
   RowBox[{"1", "}"}]}]], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "e6f0874e-c5a8-4a1a-8aa9-5402c11952ff"],
 " with all arithmetic done mod 2, so that ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  RowBox[{"1", "+", "1", "=", "0"}]], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "dbedd68c-ab4b-4357-a762-6902b50ec0e6"],
 " and vector addition is the bitwise XOR), and then scale, codes, and the \
frontier. The audience is graduate students who know quantum mechanics and \
the Pauli group but have not yet seen why a stabilizer state of a thousand \
qubits is something you can hold in your hand. Every construction in this \
document is built explicitly so you can change it, break it, and extend it. \
The ",
 ButtonBox["Wolfram QuantumFramework",
  BaseStyle->"Hyperlink",
  ButtonData->{
    URL["https://resources.wolframcloud.com/PacletRepository/resources/\
Wolfram/QuantumFramework/"], None}],
 " symbols we exercise live in the ",
 ButtonBox["Wolfram QuantumFramework",
  BaseStyle->"Hyperlink",
  ButtonData->{
    URL["https://resources.wolframcloud.com/PacletRepository/resources/\
Wolfram/QuantumFramework/"], None}],
 " paclet; the central one is PauliStabilizer."
}], "Text",ExpressionUUID->"0eced433-7ac0-4d6c-b26b-74b9bed1c62c"],

Cell["Setup", "Section",ExpressionUUID->"9989e50e-1530-4584-bbe5-ff47a417ec13"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "We load the framework from the working tree so the fast paths and recent \
fixes are present. On a current release, the plain ",
 Cell[BoxData["Needs"], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "d6077d1f-0dc9-4054-bf96-c7fd531ce4c6"],
 " line alone suffices."
}], "Text",ExpressionUUID->"ee312ce4-c389-47e4-9833-58b80296afe9"],

Cell[BoxData[{
 RowBox[{
  RowBox[{
  "PacletDirectoryLoad", 
   "[", "\"\</Users/mohammadb/Documents/GitHub/QuantumFramework/\
QuantumFramework\>\"", "]"}], ";"}], "\n", 
 RowBox[{"Needs", "[", "\"\<Wolfram`QuantumFramework`\>\"", "]"}]}], "Input",
 CellLabel->"In[1]:= ",ExpressionUUID->"10c03b23-83f7-4269-8065-e1ab5cfe0f9d"],

Cell["The core functions at a glance", "Section",ExpressionUUID->"53d8ac78-9937-4781-ae90-911b7e3f946c"],

Cell["\<\
Before the narrative, the whole working surface, grouped by task. Every call \
is exercised in context where it is introduced; this is the map.\
\>", "Text",ExpressionUUID->"bfa1e8f7-56fd-40ce-ae7a-aab3dc10ff66"],

Cell[TextData[{
 StyleBox["Construct", "TI"],
 " a register, from signed Pauli strings, a named code, or a random Clifford: \
",
 Cell[BoxData[
  RowBox[{"PauliStabilizer", "[", "n", "]"}]], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "5d0e9e9a-4c8b-405f-918f-9cbbc3721fe7"],
 ", ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  RowBox[{"PauliStabilizer", "[", 
   RowBox[{"{", 
    RowBox[{"\"\<XX\>\"", ",", " ", "\"\<ZZ\>\""}], "}"}], "]"}]], 
  "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "00b85fee-91b9-4797-9b4c-f62add639ccc"],
 ", ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  RowBox[{"PauliStabilizer", "[", "\"\<SteaneCode\>\"", "]"}]], 
  "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "dc0b4b3b-0188-496f-b6e9-2b62818b7ac9"],
 ", ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  RowBox[{"PauliStabilizer", "[", 
   RowBox[{"\"\<Random\>\"", "[", "n", "]"}], "]"}]], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "ef527d58-6e35-49ef-b66b-a2e02d73c4ce"],
 "."
}], "Item",ExpressionUUID->"263b85f9-272f-47ce-8b34-fe968e654efc"],

Cell[TextData[{
 StyleBox["Apply a Clifford gate", "TI"],
 " one at a time: ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  RowBox[{"ps", "[", 
   RowBox[{"\"\<H\>\"", ",", " ", "j"}], "]"}]], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "bf0cb9c3-6bcb-4893-90ce-5f7e177ff90f"],
 ", ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  RowBox[{"ps", "[", 
   RowBox[{"\"\<S\>\"", ",", " ", "j"}], "]"}]], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "6f67c53c-ba7e-41ab-b658-0de1b38eac78"],
 ", ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  RowBox[{"ps", "[", 
   RowBox[{"\"\<CNOT\>\"", ",", " ", "j", ",", " ", "k"}], "]"}]], 
  "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "d9e798dc-78a4-48a4-aefb-fb3ef5520400"],
 ", ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  RowBox[{"ps", "[", 
   RowBox[{"\"\<CZ\>\"", ",", " ", "j", ",", " ", "k"}], "]"}]], 
  "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "074fadf8-2acc-479e-82a8-c9dab08d3d72"],
 ", ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  RowBox[{"ps", "[", 
   RowBox[{"\"\<SWAP\>\"", ",", " ", "j", ",", " ", "k"}], "]"}]], 
  "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "58c16a3b-4d34-49fb-8491-be5aa89b6ba4"],
 "."
}], "Item",ExpressionUUID->"eed0d321-2953-43ce-8e9c-793d039b7c89"],

Cell[TextData[{
 StyleBox["Apply a whole circuit", "TI"],
 " as a gate list, routed through the compiled engine (bare names take \
default targets, ",
 Cell[BoxData["->"], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "b48f773c-a2ea-4b1f-8391-d65aab0004c1"],
 " sets explicit ones): ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  RowBox[{"ps", "[", 
   RowBox[{"{", 
    RowBox[{"\"\<H\>\"", ",", " ", "\"\<CNOT\>\"", ",", " ", 
     RowBox[{"\"\<CNOT\>\"", " ", "->", " ", 
      RowBox[{"{", 
       RowBox[{"2", ",", " ", "3"}], "}"}]}]}], "}"}], "]"}]], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "e985a162-6a34-4289-a120-ee361303dd9c"],
 "."
}], "Item",ExpressionUUID->"58a72638-70d2-4ed6-9d63-a940b82ab072"],

Cell[TextData[{
 StyleBox["Inspect", "TI"],
 ": ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  RowBox[{"ps", "[", "\"\<Stabilizers\>\"", "]"}]], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "29ff91bf-7d4e-4b57-8cef-22e3ac6c4c7d"],
 ", ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  RowBox[{"ps", "[", "\"\<Tableau\>\"", "]"}]], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "387b85a8-7cd8-4385-b3c7-10f9eb25637e"],
 ", ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  RowBox[{"ps", "[", "\"\<Matrix\>\"", "]"}]], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "afe3c033-13f8-4037-b99e-2284cfdfc0e3"],
 ", ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  RowBox[{"ps", "[", "\"\<State\>\"", "]"}]], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "883a23f1-f8a8-45fd-875c-e53b1725d739"],
 "."
}], "Item",ExpressionUUID->"a6ce51f7-f7dd-41d2-8efc-39f4acfaa048"],

Cell[TextData[{
 StyleBox["Measure", "TI"],
 ": ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  RowBox[{"ps", "[", 
   RowBox[{"\"\<M\>\"", ",", " ", "q"}], "]"}]], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "026c1593-3e4e-4d3d-adac-0010f66b67cc"],
 ", ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  RowBox[{"ps", "[", 
   RowBox[{"\"\<M\>\"", ",", " ", "\"\<ZZ\>\""}], "]"}]], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "15563a53-b20b-4e4f-bc4b-0470639e7942"],
 ", ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  RowBox[{"ps", "[", 
   RowBox[{"\"\<Expectation\>\"", ",", " ", "\"\<ZZ\>\""}], "]"}]], 
  "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "92cd55e6-c819-458e-bc57-e104e1d84830"],
 ", ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  RowBox[{"ps", "[", 
   RowBox[{"\"\<SymbolicMeasure\>\"", ",", " ", "q"}], "]"}]], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "0c6a12ab-a957-4d0d-98b2-b665ebd4f9ca"],
 "."
}], "Item",ExpressionUUID->"42e542b8-e4c7-4964-9786-3e9653b857e0"],

Cell[TextData[{
 StyleBox["Entanglement entropy", "TI"],
 " across a cut: ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  RowBox[{"ps", "[", 
   RowBox[{"\"\<Entropy\>\"", ",", " ", 
    RowBox[{"{", 
     RowBox[{"1", ",", " ", "2"}], "}"}]}], "]"}]], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "5ee98bff-8bad-4e4e-82ec-f10cf6114f0f"],
 "."
}], "Item",ExpressionUUID->"32eddbd3-6ba9-4525-965f-1a7756c05a7e"],

Cell[TextData[{
 StyleBox["Sibling heads", "TI"],
 ": ",
 Cell[BoxData["StabilizerFrame"], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "27dc7a11-8445-4a5d-b584-c79dd1cbc67b"],
 ", ",
 Cell[BoxData["CliffordChannel"], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "f7eb246f-a50f-46e5-968b-0a5c0d283175"],
 ", ",
 Cell[BoxData["GraphState"], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "f94701ab-7f84-4cf1-9b79-197841ccd4c0"],
 " with ",
 Cell[BoxData["LocalComplement"], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "0ae09820-c413-41d3-bc81-0ff817a2f5f3"],
 ", and the predicate ",
 Cell[BoxData["StabilizerStateQ"], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "c0eec50a-a541-4b00-a340-4c384971ae9a"],
 "."
}], "Item",ExpressionUUID->"a8a86356-8bbf-43e9-8f83-d830ba80c92f"],

Cell["Why stabilizers: the exponential wall", "Section",ExpressionUUID->"cd132669-59bd-4fcc-8bf5-c94d77b2ae27"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "A pure state of ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  StyleBox["n", "TI"]], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "da8539b2-0d16-43c5-bbfd-e99831f1709b"],
 " qubits is a unit vector in ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  SuperscriptBox["\:2102", 
   SuperscriptBox["2", 
    StyleBox["n", "TI"]]]], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "31af9b91-db1e-4116-9d66-5e3a386053a4"],
 ", so writing it down means storing ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  SuperscriptBox["2", 
   StyleBox["n", "TI"]]], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "530a4634-0d10-4fc7-8cfc-b0efd8ca898a"],
 " complex amplitudes. At ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  RowBox[{
   StyleBox["n", "TI"], "=", "20"}]], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "b4eaa4bf-55a3-4f13-a432-a36b8923cb5b"],
 " that is already a million numbers; at ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  RowBox[{
   StyleBox["n", "TI"], "=", "50"}]], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "c0dbc358-99a3-423b-b64c-3c66b17f33b4"],
 " it is about ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  SuperscriptBox["10", "15"]], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "e392aae8-35a8-4034-ac74-8a582c2dd33b"],
 ", a petabyte of amplitudes even at one byte each; by ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  RowBox[{
   StyleBox["n", "TI"], "=", "100"}]], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "d970bb55-7b2b-4ee9-8704-a8a25de3bc2f"],
 " it passes the number of atoms in a building (",
 Cell[BoxData[
  RowBox[{"\[Tilde]", 
   SuperscriptBox["10", "30"]}]], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "80dc89df-c359-4a9c-b77b-0f1e03e6f4ab"],
 "). Yet many of the states we care most about, including every state any \
error-correcting code protects, are not generic: they sit at the fixed points \
of a large group of Pauli operators, and that structure can be stored in ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  RowBox[{
   StyleBox["O", "TI"], 
   StyleBox["(",
    SpanMaxSize->1], 
   SuperscriptBox[
    StyleBox["n", "TI"], "2"], 
   StyleBox[")",
    SpanMaxSize->1]}]], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "c72e53e2-bb4f-4ff3-97e6-8f5d4b4aacb7"],
 " bits."
}], "Text",ExpressionUUID->"da4298b0-4c72-4800-81fa-150d3222ff31"],

Cell["\<\
To feel the wall, ask for the dense state vector of a 20-qubit GHZ state and \
look only at its length:\
\>", "Text",ExpressionUUID->"d3ee5d58-66f7-4926-bfa3-eab53d85d38c"],

Cell[CellGroupData[{

Cell[BoxData[
 RowBox[{"Length", " ", "@", " ", 
  RowBox[{
   RowBox[{"QuantumState", "[", 
    RowBox[{"\"\<GHZ\>\"", "[", "20", "]"}], "]"}], "[", "\"\<StateVector\>\"",
    "]"}]}]], "Input",
 CellLabel->"In[2]:= ",ExpressionUUID->"167461ee-14e7-4b35-b99f-b3d667b452d5"],

Cell[BoxData["1048576"], "Output",
 CellLabel->"Out[2]= ",ExpressionUUID->"381d54ad-b250-44d4-b739-69f06e004c1d"]
}, Open  ]],

Cell[TextData[{
 "That is ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  SuperscriptBox["2", "20"]], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "528e85ad-12f9-49de-822a-a996221d2664"],
 " amplitudes for a state that is pinned down completely by 20 short Pauli \
strings. The stabilizer formalism is the bookkeeping that exploits exactly \
this gap."
}], "Text",ExpressionUUID->"8c86afd9-b6fa-4487-9181-893d2340b6fe"],

Cell["A state is what fixes it: the single qubit", "Section",ExpressionUUID->"430f83cc-9f38-46f4-8650-60c64181ba4a"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "The central move is to stop describing a state by its amplitudes and start \
describing it by the operators that leave it invariant. The state ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  TemplateBox[{"0"},
   "Ket"]], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "8f840c5b-3702-4e30-8ff6-ecb28bb0c30d"],
 " is the unique ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  RowBox[{"+", "1"}]], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "ee2cf870-a8ea-4c27-8fb9-ae14777252b6"],
 " eigenvector of the Pauli operator ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  StyleBox["Z", "TI"]], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "02eb403e-7c52-49d0-b096-40ff18fe1fd6"],
 ". We say ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  StyleBox["Z", "TI"]], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "1486ad9a-61c5-4c8a-8b5f-9f255a60cda4"],
 " ",
 StyleBox["stabilizes", "TI"],
 " ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  TemplateBox[{"0"},
   "Ket"]], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "d39dd8ef-55a8-4636-91b9-9b0d81e963bf"],
 ", and since one operator already determines a one-qubit state up to \
normalization, that single fact ",
 StyleBox["is", "TI"],
 " the state."
}], "Text",ExpressionUUID->"c8a17f2e-ebe6-45dc-8354-ce0efe777484"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "A caution that defines the whole subject: this works only for special \
states. Of all one-qubit pure states, exactly six are ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  RowBox[{"+", "1"}]], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "335751a1-f534-48ac-aa8f-99b399fa3439"],
 " eigenstates of a Pauli: ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  TemplateBox[{"0"},
   "Ket"]], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "f22751f9-e74f-49b4-b7f9-377907a8797a"],
 " and ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  TemplateBox[{"1"},
   "Ket"]], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "41603048-a230-430f-bda0-bff72616341f"],
 " for ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  RowBox[{"\[PlusMinus]", 
   StyleBox["Z", "TI"]}]], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "f6470496-cf70-4d52-9174-d7c05b9da929"],
 ", ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  TemplateBox[{"\[PlusMinus]"},
   "Ket"]], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "48cc7083-c2d6-4cce-820f-301cbe474f0c"],
 " for ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  RowBox[{"\[PlusMinus]", 
   StyleBox["X", "TI"]}]], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "e2d92eb4-eb6d-41af-bd88-c7070a73b88a"],
 ", and ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  TemplateBox[{
    RowBox[{"\[PlusMinus]", 
      StyleBox["i", "TI"]}]},
   "Ket"]], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "9b14ea9c-9f0d-46fa-8fd3-918488429c01"],
 " for ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  RowBox[{"\[PlusMinus]", 
   StyleBox["Y", "TI"]}]], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "3c903fe3-e8ba-4dcd-be64-077fd39c7a1e"],
 ". These six are the ",
 StyleBox["stabilizer states", "TI"],
 ", and the formalism is exactly their theory and its multi-qubit \
generalization; a generic ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  RowBox[{
   RowBox[{
    StyleBox["cos",
     FontSlant->"Plain"], 
    StyleBox["\[Theta]", "TI"], 
    TemplateBox[{"0"},
     "Ket"]}], "+", 
   RowBox[{
    StyleBox["sin",
     FontSlant->"Plain"], 
    StyleBox["\[Theta]", "TI"], 
    TemplateBox[{"1"},
     "Ket"]}]}]], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "37347ac5-1577-492e-b100-ea6a135fd109"],
 " is fixed by no Pauli and falls outside it. What makes the restriction \
worth a whole subject is that the states it does cover are exactly the ones \
error correction and large parts of quantum algorithms are built from."
}], "Text",ExpressionUUID->"3edbe34d-6871-440f-afd6-a1f527c6d89a"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "This deserves a closer look, because \"fixed by no Pauli\" is not the same \
as \"fixed by nothing.\" ",
 StyleBox["Every", "TI"],
 " pure state is the ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  RowBox[{"+", "1"}]], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "c5ca9661-e2c0-4c62-8286-d9747c729140"],
 " eigenstate of some operator. The reflection ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  RowBox[{
   RowBox[{"2", 
    TemplateBox[{
      StyleBox["\[Psi]", "TI"]},
     "Ket"], 
    TemplateBox[{
      StyleBox["\[Psi]", "TI"]},
     "Bra"]}], "-", 
   StyleBox["I", "TI"]}]], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "c33ebe8c-9869-44d0-abb8-de150b61f95f"],
 " does the job for any ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  TemplateBox[{
    StyleBox["\[Psi]", "TI"]},
   "Ket"]], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "113e2f7d-41ac-49df-8a65-720824f046ae"],
 " at all, leaving ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  TemplateBox[{
    StyleBox["\[Psi]", "TI"]},
   "Ket"]], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "a61a1993-b282-4d41-88b8-3901b82b627a"],
 " alone and flipping the sign of everything orthogonal to it:"
}], "Text",ExpressionUUID->"96b0c126-7319-4ea4-8c91-06ef6ea5a246"],

Cell[CellGroupData[{

Cell[BoxData[{
 RowBox[{
  RowBox[{"psi", " ", "=", " ", 
   RowBox[{"{", 
    RowBox[{
     RowBox[{"Cos", "[", 
      RowBox[{"1", "/", "3"}], "]"}], ",", " ", 
     RowBox[{"Sin", "[", 
      RowBox[{"1", "/", "3"}], "]"}]}], "}"}]}], ";"}], "\n", 
 RowBox[{
  RowBox[{"reflection", " ", "=", " ", 
   RowBox[{
    RowBox[{"2", " ", 
     RowBox[{"Outer", "[", 
      RowBox[{"Times", ",", " ", "psi", ",", " ", "psi"}], "]"}]}], " ", "-", 
    " ", 
    RowBox[{"IdentityMatrix", "[", "2", "]"}]}]}], ";"}], "\n", 
 RowBox[{
  RowBox[{"Simplify", "[", 
   RowBox[{"reflection", " ", ".", " ", "psi"}], "]"}], " ", "==", " ", 
  "psi"}]}], "Input",
 CellLabel->"In[3]:= ",ExpressionUUID->"4eb397e8-ee29-45da-a16f-0f8c2978708c"],

Cell[BoxData["True"], "Output",
 CellLabel->"Out[3]= ",ExpressionUUID->"0055ed79-5d49-45c5-ab85-a4b814d6ba86"]
}, Open  ]],

Cell["\<\
That stabilizing operator is a dense, structureless thing that turns \
continuously as the state turns:\
\>", "Text",ExpressionUUID->"709b954a-a895-4af4-88af-2b09a5615ca1"],

Cell[CellGroupData[{

Cell[BoxData[
 RowBox[{
  RowBox[{"Simplify", "[", "reflection", "]"}], " ", "//", " ", 
  "MatrixForm"}]], "Input",
 CellLabel->"In[4]:= ",ExpressionUUID->"21ed0df3-97d3-43a9-8a7b-c865d34c512a"],

Cell[BoxData[
 TagBox[
  RowBox[{"(", "\[NoBreak]", GridBox[{
     {
      RowBox[{"Cos", "[", 
       FractionBox["2", "3"], "]"}], 
      RowBox[{"Sin", "[", 
       FractionBox["2", "3"], "]"}]},
     {
      RowBox[{"Sin", "[", 
       FractionBox["2", "3"], "]"}], 
      RowBox[{"-", 
       RowBox[{"Cos", "[", 
        FractionBox["2", "3"], "]"}]}]}
    },
    GridBoxAlignment->{"Columns" -> {{Center}}, "Rows" -> {{Baseline}}},
    GridBoxSpacings->{"Columns" -> {
        Offset[0.27999999999999997`], {
         Offset[0.7]}, 
        Offset[0.27999999999999997`]}, "Rows" -> {
        Offset[0.2], {
         Offset[0.4]}, 
        Offset[0.2]}}], "\[NoBreak]", ")"}],
  Function[BoxForm`e$, 
   MatrixForm[BoxForm`e$]]]], "Output",
 CellLabel->"Out[4]= ",ExpressionUUID->"1a73ebf8-6435-465f-9d59-8793f02928a7"]
}, Open  ]],

Cell[TextData[{
 "So \"a state is what fixes it\" is, on its own, vacuous: this reflection \
takes the full ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  SuperscriptBox["2", 
   StyleBox["n", "TI"]]], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "f3497af7-9669-4cc6-ae7a-50ebea5c07a1"],
 " amplitudes to write down, exactly the cost we are fleeing, and a gate \
turns it into some other arbitrary operator. The power comes entirely from \
restricting the fixing operators to the ",
 StyleBox["Pauli group", "TI"],
 ", which is special on four counts that only pay off together:"
}], "Text",ExpressionUUID->"72f0f7b2-a879-44cc-aa47-ac53cbd82cb2"],

Cell[TextData[{
 StyleBox["Cheap to name", "TI"],
 ": a Pauli string is ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  RowBox[{
   StyleBox["O", "TI"], 
   StyleBox["(",
    SpanMaxSize->1], 
   StyleBox["n", "TI"], 
   StyleBox[")",
    SpanMaxSize->1]}]], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "bb4d0e25-1bfa-4f71-9659-09986410184a"],
 " bits, two per qubit and a sign, not ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  SuperscriptBox["2", 
   StyleBox["n", "TI"]]], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "119e7330-96bb-4048-99dc-de484a11b0c6"],
 " amplitudes."
}], "Item",ExpressionUUID->"c04922e3-5dab-44b2-836e-563569bb4c51"],

Cell[TextData[{
 StyleBox["Clean spectrum", "TI"],
 ": it squares to the identity, so its eigenvalues are ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  RowBox[{"\[PlusMinus]", "1"}]], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "cea081df-775e-47f4-8e9b-1076cd74db98"],
 ", and \"fixed by ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  StyleBox["P", "TI"]], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "5cb77886-b2c1-4b67-bbc8-731b721c3195"],
 "\" sharpens to the binary fact \"",
 Cell[BoxData[
  RowBox[{"+", "1"}]], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "4e5f8e4d-4182-477f-9271-864a1c123540"],
 " eigenstate.\""
}], "Item",ExpressionUUID->"3dc57ac5-5e11-4889-bddf-a669827c3f5b"],

Cell[TextData[{
 StyleBox["Commute or anticommute", "TI"],
 ": any two Paulis do one or the other, with nothing in between, so ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  StyleBox["n", "TI"]], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "9c18fe2d-5a55-4bd3-861a-366f55591e51"],
 " independent commuting Paulis halve the ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  SuperscriptBox["2", 
   StyleBox["n", "TI"]]], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "039527ca-76ca-4439-9015-bbc994aad662"],
 "-dimensional space ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  StyleBox["n", "TI"]], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "20794c04-3216-489b-8e9b-0485c6a298ee"],
 " times and leave a unique joint ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  RowBox[{"+", "1"}]], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "19534148-062b-4ca8-87e4-71f36ac6fe38"],
 " eigenstate, which is why a list of ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  StyleBox["n", "TI"]], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "7b4ffd3f-865e-4036-8cc3-819710d01071"],
 " generators pins down one state exactly."
}], "Item",ExpressionUUID->"bdb7210b-d686-4c11-a048-1cc2ffb67f4b"],

Cell[TextData[{
 StyleBox["Closed under Clifford gates", "TI"],
 ": conjugation by ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  StyleBox["H", "TI"]], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "6aeadb35-8e62-46fa-ab0a-149b53707948"],
 ", ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  StyleBox["S", "TI"]], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "f209b621-8edf-4d69-be31-de3c7f455906"],
 ", and ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  StyleBox["CNOT",
   FontSlant->"Plain"]], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "c2fb021f-02a0-4c5c-b402-f5a5907c2326"],
 " sends Paulis to Paulis, so the description never leaves the Pauli language \
as the state evolves."
}], "Item",ExpressionUUID->"ec2e0ee2-6a59-40b8-a083-6fce9327873d"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "The reflection ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  RowBox[{
   RowBox[{"2", 
    TemplateBox[{
      StyleBox["\[Psi]", "TI"]},
     "Ket"], 
    TemplateBox[{
      StyleBox["\[Psi]", "TI"]},
     "Bra"]}], "-", 
   StyleBox["I", "TI"]}]], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "f3bd703f-2cbc-49d1-8dac-093faa6eed82"],
 " has none of these properties. Drop any one of them and naming a state by \
what fixes it stops paying its way; keep all four and it becomes the ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  RowBox[{
   StyleBox["O", "TI"], 
   StyleBox["(",
    SpanMaxSize->1], 
   SuperscriptBox[
    StyleBox["n", "TI"], "2"], 
   StyleBox[")",
    SpanMaxSize->1]}]], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "85fbba17-0a1d-4202-8cbc-117e3576ce4b"],
 " tableau the rest of this document runs on."
}], "Text",ExpressionUUID->"178195a9-3b74-44ef-b1b1-0f8f390f0ce2"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "Verify that ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  StyleBox["Z", "TI"]], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "d3c0b6a7-5bca-4f46-8d78-e4339778d011"],
 " fixes ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  TemplateBox[{"0"},
   "Ket"]], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "e4a96d38-fa32-4dea-922a-ce95d2dcb51c"],
 ", recalling that the built-in ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  RowBox[{"PauliMatrix", "[", "1", "]"}]], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "2552db02-e053-4a3e-84b8-1778d189701e"],
 ", ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  RowBox[{"PauliMatrix", "[", "2", "]"}]], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "2ed589d0-736b-414e-97b6-5bc096fc58fa"],
 ", ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  RowBox[{"PauliMatrix", "[", "3", "]"}]], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "7d0745c0-9bbe-45c1-970b-f54d0cae2da0"],
 " are ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  StyleBox["X", "TI"]], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "f7223821-da09-469b-8bf1-941480e2f4a7"],
 ", ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  StyleBox["Y", "TI"]], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "43001469-7744-49be-b307-3f5552b65731"],
 ", ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  StyleBox["Z", "TI"]], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "f9ac34c0-4562-46e1-b3ac-748cd9d54f95"],
 ":"
}], "Text",ExpressionUUID->"3040f588-74bb-48a6-945f-d6d7339fea77"],

Cell[CellGroupData[{

Cell[BoxData[
 RowBox[{
  RowBox[{
   RowBox[{"PauliMatrix", "[", "3", "]"}], " ", ".", " ", 
   RowBox[{"{", 
    RowBox[{"1", ",", " ", "0"}], "}"}]}], " ", "==", " ", 
