Cell[TextData[{
 "The two values are the post-measurement stabilizer states for outcomes ",
 Cell[BoxData["0"], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "f3e9f10b-207c-4b62-836a-ad34e37d04ff"],
 " and ",
 Cell[BoxData["1"], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "961166fc-fa10-4233-8df4-5e6ef2c283dc"],
 "; their signs differ, which is the collapse. The correlation that makes the \
Bell state interesting shows up when we measure ",
 StyleBox["every", "TI"],
 " qubit of a GHZ state: only the all-zeros and all-ones strings have nonzero \
probability."
}], "Text",ExpressionUUID->"a166ae10-15d7-4e3d-86c3-a448b1f19ebd"],

