Cell[TextData[{
 "These two trees are the branching picture, and together they show its cost \
and its blind spot. The cost is size: ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  StyleBox["r", "TI"]], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "2c3af7f0-54a2-4afb-bfb8-096d6cfe7427"],
 " undetermined measurements fork into ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  SuperscriptBox["2", 
   StyleBox["r", "TI"]]], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "03bbe585-4bdd-48e8-9678-48d064c55832"],
 " leaves, so collecting statistics means either materializing an exponential \
tree or re-walking one root-to-leaf path per sample, re-measuring every qubit \
on each walk. The blind spot is that the number of leaves is not the number \
of independent outcomes. The entire GHZ tree is generated by the single \
coin-flip at its one fork: ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  SubscriptBox[
   StyleBox["m", "TI"], "2"]], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "d2af62cb-ba49-4f4b-8498-1f745c873b9f"],
 " and ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  SubscriptBox[
   StyleBox["m", "TI"], "3"]], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "b0fd4f96-4cfb-4f39-8295-3d22f9025f4a"],
 " are not independent results but forced copies of ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  SubscriptBox[
   StyleBox["m", "TI"], "1"]], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "93f234d0-4fcf-44d8-af55-fb6d9c276990"],
 ", a relation the tree records only implicitly, in which edges happen not to \
branch. At three qubits one reads it off by eye; at a hundred, the tree is \
astronomically large while the relations among its outcomes stay linear and \
few."
}], "Text",ExpressionUUID->"91c6fa5e-af6a-4f73-8df3-273e2ecb2646"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "There is a more efficient way to handle many shots, and it keeps exactly \
that linear structure while throwing the tree away. Fang and Ying's SymPhase \
technique replaces the branching with algebra: the circuit is traversed ",
 StyleBox["once", "TI"],
 ", and each unresolved random outcome, instead of forking the history, is \
carried as a fresh formal bit ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  SubscriptBox[
   StyleBox["s", "TI"], 
   StyleBox["k", "TI"]]], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "7e0ad772-25fe-4af5-ae12-61d04eee8d16"],
 " written into a sign, an unknown that later operations can refer to by \
name. The state stays a single ",
 Cell[BoxData["PauliStabilizer"], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "c302914d-065e-46bf-b071-c59263f372b2"],
 ". A symbolic ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  StyleBox["Z", "TI"]], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "175e73e5-e0f6-442b-88c0-c6aaf98b7246"],
 "-measurement of Bell qubit 1 introduces one such bit:"
}], "Text",ExpressionUUID->"0412227a-b8bb-453b-b27c-8b26010ee0f6"],

Cell[CellGroupData[{

Cell[BoxData[
 RowBox[{"sm", " ", "=", " ", 
  RowBox[{
   RowBox[{
    RowBox[{"PauliStabilizer", "[", "2", "]"}], "[", 
    RowBox[{"{", 
     RowBox[{"\"\<H\>\"", ",", " ", "\"\<CNOT\>\""}], "}"}], "]"}], "[", 
   RowBox[{"\"\<SymbolicMeasure\>\"", ",", " ", "1"}], "]"}]}]], "Input",
 CellLabel->
