  "Out[88]= ",ExpressionUUID->"104cd908-0137-47dd-834a-655b098ddfc3"]
}, Open  ]],

Cell["and read its generators:", "Text",ExpressionUUID->"3f0be6a6-02a2-4f22-aa84-822696ec7bd6"],

Cell[CellGroupData[{

Cell[BoxData[
 RowBox[{"gs", "[", "\"\<Stabilizers\>\"", "]"}]], "Input",
 CellLabel->
  "In[89]:= ",ExpressionUUID->"ae557fbe-c50b-412a-8daf-47d62d04b623"],

Cell[BoxData[
 RowBox[{"{", 
  RowBox[{"\<\"XZIZ\"\>", ",", "\<\"ZXZI\"\>", ",", "\<\"IZXZ\"\>", 
   ",", "\<\"ZIZX\"\>"}], "}"}]], "Output",
 CellLabel->
  "Out[89]= ",ExpressionUUID->"2929ab69-b330-4ae0-bb74-be327b73e8f1"]
}, Open  ]],

Cell[TextData[{
 "Each generator is an ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  StyleBox["X", "TI"]], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "ecd7e33e-deb7-4ef9-a652-1b4b1172044d"],
 " on one vertex dressed by ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  StyleBox["Z", "TI"]], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "134ff1c3-2369-4a22-9ee6-a2c0f5004d7f"],
 " on its neighbors, the cluster-state structure. A graph state is an \
ordinary stabilizer state, so it converts to a ",
 Cell[BoxData["PauliStabilizer"], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "e17d5908-70a2-4eae-a8d4-c7564e79e35f"],
 " and answers the same questions. The 4-cycle cluster carries two bits of \
entanglement across the cut ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  RowBox[{
   RowBox[{"{", "1"}], ",", 
   RowBox[{"2", "}", "\[VerticalSeparator]", "{", "3"}], ",", 
   RowBox[{"4", "}"}]}]], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "3e928865-ecfa-4a4d-a0db-5b9fbe3c6783"],
 ", one per edge crossing it:"
}], "Text",ExpressionUUID->"3ab86c2b-0261-496b-ba74-8e2d65c5955d"],

Cell[CellGroupData[{

Cell[BoxData[
 RowBox[{"{", 
  RowBox[{
   RowBox[{"StabilizerStateQ", "[", 
    RowBox[{"gs", "[", "\"\<PauliStabilizer\>\"", "]"}], "]"}], ",", " ", 
   RowBox[{
    RowBox[{"gs", "[", "\"\<PauliStabilizer\>\"", "]"}], "[", 
    RowBox[{"\"\<Entropy\>\"", ",", " ", 
     RowBox[{"{", 
      RowBox[{"1", ",", " ", "2"}], "}"}]}], "]"}]}], "}"}]], "Input",
 CellLabel->
  "In[90]:= ",ExpressionUUID->"c7101e05-3a45-4b00-8be7-e5587e7f322e"],

Cell[BoxData[
 RowBox[{"{", 
  RowBox[{"True", ",", "2"}], "}"}]], "Output",
 CellLabel->
  "Out[90]= ",ExpressionUUID->"c8537f94-926c-442b-a594-cbc70dc6c4f7"]
}, Open  ]],

Cell[TextData[{
 "The graph is a far more compact record than the tableau when the state is \
sparse. A path graph gives the one-dimensional cluster state of \
measurement-based computation, each generator a local ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  StyleBox[
   RowBox[{"X", "Z"}], "TI"]], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "8d96f2fb-887a-4e67-977c-8edc70746a50"],
 " pattern:"
}], "Text",ExpressionUUID->"5bf87215-843e-4fbb-80f7-13ba004f022e"],

Cell[CellGroupData[{

Cell[BoxData[
 RowBox[{
  RowBox[{"GraphState", "[", 
   RowBox[{"PathGraph", "[", 
    RowBox[{"Range", "[", "3", "]"}], "]"}], "]"}], "[", "\"\<Stabilizers\>\"",
   "]"}]], "Input",
 CellLabel->
  "In[91]:= ",ExpressionUUID->"8bf44d8d-8410-42ff-802e-2c9bab2a8e6f"],

Cell[BoxData[
 RowBox[{"{", 
  RowBox[{"\<\"XZI\"\>", ",", "\<\"ZXZ\"\>", ",", "\<\"IZX\"\>"}], 
  "}"}]], "Output",
 CellLabel->
  "Out[91]= ",ExpressionUUID->"6f4aa042-1e53-4454-b14f-1a1f11dc3fce"]
}, Open  ]],

Cell[TextData[{
 "The operation that moves through the local-Clifford equivalence class is ",
 StyleBox["local complementation", "TI"],
 ", which toggles the edges among the neighbors of a chosen vertex; here it \
is ",
 Cell[BoxData["LocalComplement"], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "7f852d68-0473-4044-824c-44fa1a538541"],
 ". Local-complementing the 4-cycle at vertex 1 adds the edge between its two \
neighbors:"
}], "Text",ExpressionUUID->"83292b46-e6de-4175-a0fb-a1b05ee924f0"],

Cell[CellGroupData[{

Cell[BoxData[
 RowBox[{"EdgeList", "[", 
  RowBox[{"LocalComplement", "[", 
   RowBox[{
    RowBox[{"CycleGraph", "[", "4", "]"}], ",", " ", "1"}], "]"}], 
  "]"}]], "Input",
 CellLabel->
  "In[92]:= ",ExpressionUUID->"f41a550c-fcb0-4b3c-bfd8-21dab15468b2"],

Cell[BoxData[
 RowBox[{"{", 
  RowBox[{
   RowBox[{"1", "\[UndirectedEdge]", "2"}], ",", 
   RowBox[{"1", "\[UndirectedEdge]", "4"}], ",", 
   RowBox[{"2", "\[UndirectedEdge]", "3"}], ",", 
   RowBox[{"2", "\[UndirectedEdge]", "4"}], ",", 
   RowBox[{"3", "\[UndirectedEdge]", "4"}]}], "}"}]], "Output",
 CellLabel->
  "Out[92]= ",ExpressionUUID->"e38ced8a-4873-4b80-8f36-4df3f6b44bae"]
}, Open  ]],

Cell["\<\
The graph is updated correctly, but the accompanying single-qubit Clifford \
corrections, the vertex operators that would make the equivalence exact at \
the state level, are not yet tracked. Use this for graph surgery rather than \
for exact state identity.\
\>", "Text",ExpressionUUID->"ee867bae-0840-4a8b-a733-65f1d1738b6a"],

Cell["Magic and stabilizer rank", "Subsection",ExpressionUUID->"d4853d85-ace1-41bb-91bd-b3f4bea9a1c5"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "Clifford gates keep us inside the stabilizer world; a non-Clifford gate \
such as ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  StyleBox["T", "TI"]], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "2139b39b-c984-49e7-8429-e180e94a3512"],
 " does not. The framework represents a state that has left the stabilizer \
manifold as a ",
 Cell[BoxData["StabilizerFrame"], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "8bef1799-5433-4b5f-9455-5fa1df2de541"],
 ", a superposition ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  RowBox[{
   UnderscriptBox["\[Sum]", 
    StyleBox["i", "TI"],
    LimitsPositioning->False], 
   RowBox[{
    SubscriptBox[
     StyleBox["c", "TI"], 
     StyleBox["i", "TI"]], 
    TemplateBox[{
      SubscriptBox[
       StyleBox["s", "TI"], 
       StyleBox["i", "TI"]]},
     "Ket"]}]}]], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "3b35071c-274d-498c-92a8-06892a56f117"],
 " of stabilizer states. Because ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  StyleBox["T", "TI"]], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "6dec757f-4227-407b-9a5b-a0ce00d3b7ed"],
 " turns one Pauli into a sum of two, as in ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  RowBox[{
   StyleBox["T", "TI"], 
   StyleBox["X", "TI"], 
   SuperscriptBox[
    StyleBox["T", "TI"], "\[Dagger]"], "=", 
   StyleBox["(",
    SpanMaxSize->1], 
   RowBox[{
    StyleBox["X", "TI"], "+", 
    StyleBox["Y", "TI"]}], 
   StyleBox[")",
    SpanMaxSize->1], "/", 
   SqrtBox["2"]}]], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "67378c31-25a1-4cb7-a23f-a119d9ae5509"],
 ", each ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  StyleBox["T", "TI"]], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "e83a16e3-c0f7-4199-8472-98c80a09f48e"],
 " gate at most ",
 StyleBox["doubles", "TI"],
 " the number of stabilizer terms. The term count is the ",
 StyleBox["stabilizer rank", "TI"],
 ", the quantity that controls the cost of classically simulating magic, in \
the sense of Bravyi and Gosset. Watch it double, gate by gate. A helper \
reports the term count, with a bare ",
 Cell[BoxData["PauliStabilizer"], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "b2c372e9-86a3-433b-8621-ffda15db858d"],
 " counting as rank 1 and a frame as its component count:"
}], "Text",ExpressionUUID->"86853459-e80d-4f9d-928e-42e68ad77e36"],

Cell[BoxData[
 RowBox[{
  RowBox[{"stabRank", "[", "x_", "]"}], " ", ":=", " ", 
  RowBox[{"If", "[", 
   RowBox[{
    RowBox[{"MatchQ", "[", 
     RowBox[{"x", ",", " ", "_StabilizerFrame"}], "]"}], ",", " ", 
    RowBox[{"x", "[", "\"\<Length\>\"", "]"}], ",", " ", "1"}], 
   "]"}]}]], "Input",
 CellLabel->
  "In[93]:= ",ExpressionUUID->"9d694a0b-d095-4f45-8544-56d8d627f587"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "Apply ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  StyleBox["k", "TI"]], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "fb7d1873-6482-4e0d-9863-2f2b2ca7f313"],
 " successive ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  StyleBox["T", "TI"]], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "3dd4aba1-6ff9-41f9-a9a5-bfe3582af000"],
 " gates to ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  TemplateBox[{"+"},
   "Ket"]], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "b9271480-3a5f-46b0-b27f-35ff46b6d9e3"],
 " and tabulate the rank:"
}], "Text",ExpressionUUID->"f7efd58c-741f-445c-b04c-7667ade15160"],

Cell[CellGroupData[{

Cell[BoxData[
 RowBox[{"Table", "[", 
  RowBox[{
   RowBox[{"{", 
    RowBox[{"k", ",", " ", 
     RowBox[{"stabRank", "[", 
      RowBox[{
       RowBox[{"PauliStabilizer", "[", "1", "]"}], "[", 
       RowBox[{"Join", "[", 
        RowBox[{
         RowBox[{"{", "\"\<H\>\"", "}"}], ",", " ", 
         RowBox[{"Table", "[", 
          RowBox[{"\"\<T\>\"", ",", " ", "k"}], "]"}]}], "]"}], "]"}], 
      "]"}]}], "}"}], ",", " ", 
   RowBox[{"{", 
    RowBox[{"k", ",", " ", "0", ",", " ", "5"}], "}"}]}], "]"}]], "Input",
 CellLabel->
  "In[94]:= ",ExpressionUUID->"b090d22e-faba-4e51-96cf-9f04317bc1d0"],

Cell[BoxData[
 RowBox[{"{", 
  RowBox[{
   RowBox[{"{", 
    RowBox[{"0", ",", "1"}], "}"}], ",", 
   RowBox[{"{", 
    RowBox[{"1", ",", "2"}], "}"}], ",", 
   RowBox[{"{", 
    RowBox[{"2", ",", "4"}], "}"}], ",", 
   RowBox[{"{", 
    RowBox[{"3", ",", "8"}], "}"}], ",", 
   RowBox[{"{", 
    RowBox[{"4", ",", "16"}], "}"}], ",", 
   RowBox[{"{", 
    RowBox[{"5", ",", "32"}], "}"}]}], "}"}]], "Output",
 CellLabel->
  "Out[94]= ",ExpressionUUID->"6cf019de-1ddc-4f47-8a58-304d4eebd6c0"]
}, Open  ]],

Cell[TextData[{
 "The rank goes ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  RowBox[{
   RowBox[{"1", ",", "2", ",", "4"}], ",", "\[Ellipsis]", ",", 
   SuperscriptBox["2", 
    StyleBox["k", "TI"]]}]], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "22fb35fa-35fd-4114-a621-a8c8f4cfe70b"],
 ": the exponential cost of magic made concrete, and the reason a ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  StyleBox["T", "TI"]], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "c64eecda-b1bb-46fe-91b3-cf53450d40cf"],
 "-rich circuit is hard where a Clifford circuit is easy. The rank tracks the \
amount of magic, not the size of the register. Three ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  StyleBox["T", "TI"]], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "2e49032b-3aac-4abc-b579-31dc2b0fba71"],
 " gates on a Clifford backbone of growing width keep the component count \
pinned at ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  RowBox[{
   SuperscriptBox["2", "3"], "=", "8"}]], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "a62783bd-0c51-460a-970e-218c4707d3cb"],
 ", while the dense state vector it stands for grows as ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  SuperscriptBox["2", 
   StyleBox["n", "TI"]]], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "d174867b-6dbc-401e-9f81-0b3ff10183f8"],
 ". A helper builds that family, three ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  StyleBox["T", "TI"]], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "15b951d2-a453-4b19-ad57-cad6876e3c6e"],
 " gates on top of an ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  StyleBox["n", "TI"]], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "044074fe-c7e8-45e6-b3d6-5e9016db5ed2"],
 "-qubit GHZ-like state:"
}], "Text",ExpressionUUID->"2d0d4779-602b-4d5c-9a7f-3821e6254ed4"],

Cell[BoxData[
 RowBox[{
  RowBox[{"magicState", "[", "n_", "]"}], " ", ":=", " ", 
  RowBox[{
   RowBox[{"PauliStabilizer", "[", "n", "]"}], "[", 
   RowBox[{"Join", "[", 
    RowBox[{
     RowBox[{"{", 
      RowBox[{"\"\<H\>\"", " ", "->", " ", "1"}], "}"}], ",", " ", 
     RowBox[{"Table", "[", 
      RowBox[{
       RowBox[{"\"\<CNOT\>\"", " ", "->", " ", 
        RowBox[{"{", 
         RowBox[{"i", ",", " ", 
          RowBox[{"i", " ", "+", " ", "1"}]}], "}"}]}], ",", " ", 
       RowBox[{"{", 
        RowBox[{"i", ",", " ", "1", ",", " ", 
         RowBox[{"n", " ", "-", " ", "1"}]}], "}"}]}], "]"}], ",", " ", 
     RowBox[{"{", 
      RowBox[{
       RowBox[{"\"\<T\>\"", " ", "->", " ", "1"}], ",", " ", 
       RowBox[{"\"\<T\>\"", " ", "->", " ", "2"}], ",", " ", 
       RowBox[{"\"\<T\>\"", " ", "->", " ", "3"}]}], "}"}]}], "]"}], 
   "]"}]}]], "Input",
 CellLabel->
  "In[95]:= ",ExpressionUUID->"8cedb6eb-c239-4b2c-a82d-95d876ba2f7e"],

